# .env
# Parallax env. This file is COMMITTED and meant to hold dotenvx ciphertext only.
#
# Do NOT paste raw secrets here as plaintext. Encrypt each one with dotenvx-ops
# (private keys stay in your Ops login, never on disk):
#
#   curl -sfS https://dotenvx.sh/ops | sh   # once
#   dotenvx-ops login                        # once
#   npx dotenvx set GEMINI_API_KEY <value> -f .env
#   npx dotenvx set PARALLAX_TOKEN <value> -f .env
#
# `dotenvx set` rewrites the line below as `encrypted:...` and adds a
# DOTENV_PUBLIC_KEY header. Workers read the decrypted value at runtime via
# `npm run dev:gemini` / `dev:render` (which wrap the command in `dotenvx run`).

